# .roadmap.quantum — qpu_bridge bio integration

> ⚛ external quantum-resource bridge for bio/molecular structure.
> hexa-bio consumer of `~/core/qmirror` (ANU QRNG + Aer state-vector
> simulator), composed into a VQE pipeline for molecular ground-state
> energy. Cross-cutting state → `.roadmap.hexa_bio`.

**Last sync**: 2026-05-06 · **Status**: Phase 1 LANDED + production smoke (spectroscopic accuracy) · **Cycle**: 26 (qpu_bridge L1)

**Canonical doc**: [`docs/qpu_bridge_bio_application.md`](docs/qpu_bridge_bio_application.md) (§1–§17)

---

## Terminal goal

분자 Hamiltonian → Pauli string → variational ansatz → ground-state
energy 의 end-to-end pipeline. Scope ladder:

1. **L0 — H₂ minimal-basis (2 qubit, 6 Pauli terms)** — spec proof. ⬛ **CLOSED 2026-05-06**: end-to-end 0.4 µHa from E0 (spectroscopic accuracy).
2. **L1 — small-molecule generalize** (LiH 4 qubit, BeH₂ 6 qubit) — single ansatz pattern, multiple Hamiltonian.
3. **L2 — bond-length / reaction-coordinate scan** — dissociation curve / activation energy reproduction.
4. **L3 — drug-target binding pocket fragment** (single active site QM/MM split, single-restart VQE).
5. **L4 — protein-relevant subsystem (예: 활성부위 single-residue)** — pharma-application reach.

Cell DoD pattern (per molecule / system): Hamiltonian Pauli-decomposed
(literature or PySCF) → ansatz QASM3 → energy(θ) → optimizer → E_min
within published reference error band → witness row to
`state/discovery_absorption/registry.jsonl` schema
`raw_77_quantum_vqe_v1` (lands §STALLED draft when L1 first cell ships).

